feral kitten keeps on meowing i'm working on a feral kitten and he lets me touch him and hold him but if he isn't tired he meows like a siamese cat if anyone has ever had a siamese they know what i'm talking about the howling anyways so he starts to howl in my arms if he isn't tired so i let him down he goes behind a chair and gets lost and starts to howl some more so i put him back in his cage and he just keeps on howling its not food or water because he has those consistantly help i'm going out of my mind he's calling for his mother and litter mates have some compassion feral animals aren't used to people so they aren't comforted by being around us get him a stuffed animal to snuggle with and he will learn to relax more or if you really can't stand it find a foster mom for him to stay with for a while until he gets used to people Cat Socialization Feral cat Gray Wolf Feral Coyote Kitten Pet skunk Garfield Hamster RuneScape quests Siamese (cat) Feral child Dog Tag Ferret Onomatopoeia Treecat Social rule The Boy Who Knew Too Much Milton H. Erickson Purr Guinea pig Feral cat colony Peafowl Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Maine Coon The Amber Spyglass Ralston Purina Company Phoebe Buffay's songs Domestic rabbit Beat generation B3ta Taikyoku shogi Kender Friends Pok__mon Chronicles Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Pitaten Stewie Griffin Shaggy dog story Dai dai shogi Luke Skywalker Magical objects in Harry Potter The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Domestication Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Mattress The Shining (film) Kodocha The Inside Balinese (cat) Red Squirrel Polymorphism in object-oriented programming Ron and Fez Chinchilla Parade (military) Tai shogi Humphrey Bogart Descendants of Darkness Fancy rat Animal communication Jiddu Krishnamurti Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism The Critic Manx (cat) Softball Kangaroo Bobcat 2000 Australian Grand Prix Saw II Tigon Feral children in mythology and fiction 